org.csdgn.amf3

Class AmfObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.csdgn.amf3.AmfValue
      • org.csdgn.amf3.AmfObject

  • public class AmfObject
extends AmfValue
    Associated with the AMF object type. This handles ActionScript Objects and custom user classes. Traits are used to describe the attributes of a custom user class.
    Author:
    Robert Maupin

    • Constructor Detail

      • AmfObject

        public AmfObject()
        Constructs a AmfObject. By default, the object is not dynamic, is not externalizable (and the custom data is null) and has no trait name, and has an empty sealed and dynamic map.

        Description copied from class: AmfValue
        This determines if the given AmfValue equals another AmfValue exactly. The identities of the two objects do not need to match. This method is used in building the string and object reference tables.

      • getDynamicMap

        public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,AmfValue> getDynamicMap()
        Gets the dynamic map associated with this object. If the object is not dynamic, the map will be empty. Unless isDynamic() is set however the values stored in this map will not be saved into an AMF object.
        Returns:
        The map associated with the dynamic portion of this object.

      • isDynamic

        public boolean isDynamic()
        This is a convenience method that is exactly the same as returned by Trait.isDynamic() method returned in the getTrait() method of this class. It indicates if this object is considered dynamic or not, which determines if the dynamic portion of this AmfObject will be stored.
        Returns:
        If the object is dynamic.

      • isExternalizable

        public boolean isExternalizable()
        This is a convenience method that is exactly the same as returned by Trait.isExternalizable() method returned in the getTrait() method of this class. It indicates if this object is considered externalizable or not, which determines if the externalizable object of this AmfObject will be stored.
        Returns:
        If the object is dynamic.

      • setDynamic

        public void setDynamic(boolean isDynamic)
        Determines if this object is dynamic and if the dynamic section will be stored on writing.
        Parameters:
        isDynamic - true if the object has a dynamic section, false otherwise.

      • setExternalizable

        public void setExternalizable(boolean isExternalizable)
        Determines if this object has externalizable data and if the externalizable data will be written when writing to an AMF. If the ExternalizableObject is null this value will be treated as false when writing, regardless of its actual value.
        Parameters:
        isExternalizable - true to write externalizable data, false otherwise

      • setExternalizableObject
